gomodel:SYNGO_2634  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.8; \"ABHD17 specifically mediates PSD-95 depalmitoylation in neurons. \"\n- \"When we simultaneously knocked-down ABHD17A, 17B, and 17C by the AAV-miRNA vector (Fig. 3E), ... Importantly, triple-knockdown of ABHD17 members apparently delayed PSD-95 depalmitoylation process (Fig. 8A, B) and significantly prolonged the half-life of palmitate on PSD-95 to 4.8 ± 1.3 h (Fig. 8D). When neurons were treated with 2-BP for 2 h, the intensity of synaptic PSD-95 clusters was significantly reduced (Fig. 8E,F), indicating rapid depalmitoylation of PSD-95 at local synapses. Consistent with biochemical data, this reduction of PSD-95 clusters was significantly suppressed in neurons in which ABHD17 members were knocked-down. \"\n\nFig.3: ABHD17C is also present in the PSD-95 fraction.. Experimental description: \"Differential subcellular distribution of FLAG-tagged ABHD proteins and Lypla2. Note that some populations of ABHD17A localized at the postsynaptic membranes labeled by pan-Shank antibody (red) in 14 DIV rat hippocampal neurons.\"\n\n- \"The cDNAs of rat ...ABHD17A (NM_001006983), ... ABHD17B (NM_146096), ABHD17C (NM_133722), ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2634" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

